---
description: Core coding guidelines for the Xentom integrations monorepo
alwaysApply: true
---

Read and follow all rules, conventions, and patterns defined in the `AGENTS.md` file at the repository root. It is the canonical source of truth for this codebase and covers:

- Stack and tooling (Bun, Turbo, TypeScript, Biome, Valibot)
- Available commands (root-level and per-package)
- Quality gates (typecheck, lint, format — all must pass with zero errors and zero warnings)
- Package structure and file organization
- Import conventions and forbidden patterns
- Entry point patterns (auth, state, lifecycle)
- Pin definitions and rules
- Node definitions and rules
- Select controls with dynamic options
- Type safety requirements
- Framework API reference locations

Always use Bun. Never use npm or yarn.
